# Product Launch Playbook

A framework for planning and executing successful product launches.

Launching a product requires coordination across multiple teams including product, engineering, marketing, and customer support.

This playbook outlines the steps required for successful product releases.

---

# Purpose

The goal of product launch planning is to:

• ensure product readiness  
• align internal teams  
• communicate value to users  
• support adoption after launch

---

# Launch Phases

Product launches typically follow several phases.

Planning  
↓  
Preparation  
↓  
Release  
↓  
Post-Launch Evaluation

---

# Launch Preparation

Teams should confirm:

• product functionality is complete  
• quality assurance testing is finished  
• documentation is prepared  
• customer support teams are ready

---

# Launch Communication

Launch communication may include:

• product announcements  
• marketing campaigns  
• internal team briefings  
• customer documentation

---

# Post-Launch Evaluation

After launch, teams should review:

• product adoption  
• user engagement  
• customer feedback  
• performance metrics

Launch evaluation helps guide future product improvements.
